In response to: Rabies - Indonesia (09): (Bali) 20110404.1043
-------------------------------------------------------------
For your information, we all do know we must continue to run the
vaccination program and the plan is to start again as soon as possible
by 1 May 2011 at the latest, again island-wide. We will booster all
previously vaccinated dogs (with the exception of those we are
positive were vaccinated in the previous month) and vaccinate all
newcomers into the dog population here. We also vaccinate all pet
macaques we come across and cats that have owners and can hold them.

We don't have the capacity to vaccinate all "outdoor" cats, and as
you mention [see statement by Merritt Clifton below] don't need to
focus on them. We have had several cats test positive for rabies, and
one cat had bitten the family it lives with so they had to receive
post-exposure [prophylaxis] and we continue to educate the community
in regards to post-exposure.

--
communicated by:
Janice Girardi
Bali Animal Welfare Association
Bali, Indonesia
<Bawabali@aol.com>

